  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 4px;
}

.typing-indicator span {
  width: 6px;
  height: 6px;
  background-color: var(--text-tertiary);
  border-radius: 50%;
  animation: typing-pulse 1.2s ease-in-out infinite;
}

.typing-indicator span:nth-child(2) {
  animation-delay: 0.2s;
}

.typing-indicator span:nth-child(3) {
  animation-delay: 0.4s;
}

@keyframes typing-pulse {
  0%, 60%, 100% {
    transform: scale(1);
    opacity: 0.4;
  }
  30% {
    transform: scale(1.2);
    opacity: 1;
  }
}
```

**Verdict:** ✅ **NO CONFLICT** — There's only one definition with `display: inline-flex` and `gap: 4px`. No conflicting layout or padding.

---

### **2. Title bar offset hard-coded 80px (High) — LEGIT ✓**

**Finding:** Hard-coded 80px padding for macOS traffic lights confirmed.

**Code from TitleBar.css (lines 20-27):**
```css
.title-bar-brand {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 10px;
  padding-left: 80px; /* Space for macOS traffic lights + breathing room */
  flex-shrink: 0;
  white-space: nowrap;
}
```

**Verdict:** 🔴 **LEGIT ISSUE** — The 80px left padding is hard-coded. On non-macOS systems (Windows/Linux) or when the titlebar doesn't have traffic lights, this creates excessive wasted space. Consider using a CSS variable or detecting the OS/titlebar state.

---

### **3. CodeMirror dark: true always (High) — ALREADY FIXED ✓**

**Finding:** The theme is **dynamic**, not hard-coded to `dark: true`.

**Code from editor-theme.js (lines 27-28 and 219):**
```javascript
export function createGraphiteTheme(isDark = true) {
  return EditorView.theme({
    // ... styles
  }, { dark: isDark });  // ← isDark parameter is used!
}
```

**Verdict:** ✅ **NOT AN ISSUE** — The `isDark` parameter is properly passed to the `EditorView.theme()` call. The function accepts a parameter and defaults to `true`, but it can be called with `isDark: false` for light themes. The implementation is correct.

---

### **4. Preview column left-aligned (High) — ALREADY FIXED ✓**

**Finding:** Preview IS centered with proper max-width constraint.

**Code from Preview.css (lines 9-20):**
```css
.preview-scroll-container {
  padding: 32px 40px;
  width: 100%;
  box-sizing: border-box;
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center;    /* ← Centered! */
}

.preview-content {
  width: 100%;
  max-width: 720px;           /* ← Fixed max-width */
}
```

**Verdict:** ✅ **ALREADY FIXED** — The preview uses `display: flex; justify-content: center;` on the scroll container, which centers the content with a `max-width: 720px`. This matches the design intent.

---

### **5. Dropdown overflow — Theme switcher (High) — ALREADY FIXED ✓**

**Finding:** Theme switcher **HAS viewport clamping** with proper edge detection.

**Code from ThemeSwitcher.jsx (lines 71-107):**
```javascript
useEffect(() => {
  if (!isOpen) return;

  const positionDropdown = () => {
    if (!triggerRef.current || !dropdownRef.current) return;

    const padding = 8;
    const triggerRect = triggerRef.current.getBoundingClientRect();
    const menuRect = dropdownRef.current.getBoundingClientRect();
    const viewportWidth = window.innerWidth;
    const viewportHeight = window.innerHeight;

    // Align right edge to trigger by default
    let left = triggerRect.right - menuRect.width;
    let top = triggerRect.bottom + 4;

    if (left < padding) left = padding;
    if (left + menuRect.width > viewportWidth - padding) {
      left = Math.max(padding, viewportWidth - padding - menuRect.width);
    }

    if (top + menuRect.height > viewportHeight - padding) {
      top = Math.max(padding, viewportHeight - padding - menuRect.height);
    }

    setDropdownStyle({ left: `${left}px`, top: `${top}px` });
  };
  // ...
}, [isOpen]);
```

**Verdict:** ✅ **ALREADY FIXED** — Implements proper viewport clamping:
- Checks left/right edges with 8px padding
- Checks bottom edge and repositions upward if needed
- Handles all viewport collision scenarios

---

### **6. Dropdown overflow — AI model picker (High) — ALREADY FIXED ✓**

**Finding:** AI model dropdown **HAS viewport clamping** with proper edge detection, matching ThemeSwitcher.

**Code from AIChat.jsx (lines 255-295):**
```javascript
useEffect(() => {
  if (!showModelPicker) return undefined;

  const positionDropdown = () => {
    if (!modelButtonRef.current || !modelDropdownRef.current) return;

    const padding = 8;
    const triggerRect = modelButtonRef.current.getBoundingClientRect();
    const menuRect = modelDropdownRef.current.getBoundingClientRect();
    const viewportWidth = window.innerWidth;
    const viewportHeight = window.innerHeight;

    let left = triggerRect.left;
    let top = triggerRect.top - menuRect.height - 4;

    if (left < padding) left = padding;
    if (left + menuRect.width > viewportWidth - padding) {
      left = Math.max(padding, viewportWidth - padding - menuRect.width);
    }

    if (top < padding) {
      top = triggerRect.bottom + 4;  // ← Flip below if no room above
    }

    if (top + menuRect.height > viewportHeight - padding) {
      top = Math.max(padding, viewportHeight - padding - menuRect.height);
    }

    setModelDropdownStyle({ left: `${left}px`, top: `${top}px` });
  };
  // ...
}, [showModelPicker]);
```

**Verdict:** ✅ **ALREADY FIXED** — Implements proper viewport clamping:
- Checks left/right edges with 8px padding
- Tries to position above first, flips below if no room
- Clamps vertically if dropdown is too tall
- Matches/improves on ContextMenu implementation

---

