**Verdict:** ALREADY FIXED. h4-h6 have `font-size: 15.5px` with `font-weight: 600`, not collapsed to body text size. This is visually distinct.

---

### **14. Chevron rotation redundancy (Low)**
**Status: LEGIT ✓**

**Code:**
```css
/* FileExplorer.css - FileNode chevron rotation */
.file-node-chevron {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  width: 16px;
  height: 16px;
  flex-shrink: 0;
  color: var(--text-tertiary);
  transition: transform 150ms ease;  /* Line 150 */
}

.file-node-chevron.expanded {
  transform: rotate(90deg);  /* Line 154 */
}

/* animations.css - Generic chevron rotation */
.chevron {
  transition: transform 150ms ease;  /* Line 47 */
}

.chevron.open {
  transform: rotate(90deg);  /* Line 51 */
}
```

**Verdict:** LEGIT REDUNDANCY. There are two separate rotation systems:
1. **FileNode-specific:** `.file-node-chevron.expanded` with `.expanded` class
2. **Generic animation system:** `.chevron.open` with `.open` class

Both rotate 90deg with identical transitions. This creates code duplication and potential confusion about which system to use.

---

